    {
      "id": "MJUe",
      "code_hash": "29a444d191592def64f5c7c1bedce09b",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h1 id=\"communities-clustering\">Communities &amp; Clustering</h1>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">Networks often have <strong>community structure</strong> \u2014 groups of nodes that are densely connected internally but sparsely connected to the rest of the network.</span>\n<h2 id=\"what-is-a-community\">What is a Community?</h2>\n<blockquote>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">A <strong>community</strong> is a set of nodes that have more connections within the group than expected by chance.</span>\n</blockquote>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">Real-world examples:</span>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Social networks</strong>: Friend groups, families, colleagues</li>\n<li><strong>Citation networks</strong>: Research communities (ML, biology, physics)</li>\n<li><strong>Biological networks</strong>: Protein complexes, functional modules</li>\n<li><strong>The web</strong>: Pages on related topics</li>\n</ul></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
    },
    {
      "id": "vblA",
      "code_hash": "2fd0b4d12f458a0e3b1f5690a051e93e",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h2 id=\"modularity-measuring-community-quality\">Modularity: Measuring Community Quality</h2>\n<span class=\"paragraph\"><strong>Modularity</strong> (<marimo-tex class=\"arithmatex\">||(Q||)</marimo-tex>) is a score that measures how good a community division is:</span>\n<marimo-tex class=\"arithmatex\">||[Q = \\frac{1}{2m} \\sum_{ij} \\left[ A_{ij} - \\frac{k_i k_j}{2m} \\right] \\delta(c_i, c_j)||]</marimo-tex><ul>\n<li><marimo-tex class=\"arithmatex\">||(A_{ij}||)</marimo-tex>: adjacency matrix (1 if edge exists)</li>\n<li><marimo-tex class=\"arithmatex\">||(k_i||)</marimo-tex>: degree of node <marimo-tex class=\"arithmatex\">||(i||)</marimo-tex></li>\n<li><marimo-tex class=\"arithmatex\">||(m||)</marimo-tex>: total number of edges</li>\n<li><marimo-tex class=\"arithmatex\">||(\\delta(c_i, c_j)||)</marimo-tex>: 1 if nodes are in same community, 0 otherwise</li>\n</ul>\n<span class=\"paragraph\"><strong>Key insight</strong>: Modularity compares the actual number of edges within communities to the expected number in a random graph with the same degree distribution.</span>\n<ul>\n<li><marimo-tex class=\"arithmatex\">||(Q &gt; 0||)</marimo-tex>: More edges within groups than expected \u2192 community structure</li>\n<li><marimo-tex class=\"arithmatex\">||(Q &gt; 0.3||)</marimo-tex>: Generally considered significant</li>\n<li><marimo-tex class=\"arithmatex\">||(Q &gt; 0.7||)</marimo-tex>: Strong community structure</li>\n</ul></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
    },
    {
      "id": "bkHC",
      "code_hash": "6a6ce0f5c281fa1968c3c859a1f5c570",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h2 id=\"community-detection-algorithms\">Community Detection Algorithms</h2>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">We'll explore three popular algorithms:</span></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
    },
    {
      "id": "lEQa",
      "code_hash": "d1076c23ea8a0806ec9abf5b27947e75",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h3 id=\"1-greedy-modularity-clauset-newman-moore\">1. Greedy Modularity (Clauset-Newman-Moore)</h3>\n<span class=\"paragraph\"><strong>How it works</strong>:</span>\n<ol>\n<li>Start with every node as its own community</li>\n<li>Repeatedly merge communities that increase modularity the most</li>\n<li>Stop when no merge improves modularity</li>\n</ol>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">\u2705 Fast (<marimo-tex class=\"arithmatex\">||(\\mathcal{O}(n \\log^2 n)||)</marimo-tex>)\n\u2705 Works well for many networks\n\u274c Can miss small communities (resolution limit)</span></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
    },
    {
      "id": "PKri",
      "code_hash": "1050e053553b96487206c09102bfe743",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h3 id=\"2-label-propagation\">2. Label Propagation</h3>\n<span class=\"paragraph\"><strong>How it works</strong>:</span>\n<ol>\n<li>Assign each node a unique label</li>\n<li>Repeatedly update each node's label to the most frequent label among its neighbors</li>\n<li>Converges when labels stop changing</li>\n</ol>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">\u2705 Very fast (<marimo-tex class=\"arithmatex\">||(\\mathcal{O}(E)||)</marimo-tex> per iteration)\n\u2705 No need to specify number of communities\n\u274c Can be unstable (different runs may give different results)</span></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
    },
    {
      "id": "Xref",
      "code_hash": "669f91e7d2860b458f8e91076a76cc0b",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h3 id=\"3-girvan-newman\">3. Girvan-Newman</h3>\n<span class=\"paragraph\"><strong>How it works</strong>:</span>\n<ol>\n<li>Compute edge betweenness for all edges</li>\n<li>Remove the edge with highest betweenness</li>\n<li>Recompute betweenness</li>\n<li>Repeat until graph is partitioned</li>\n</ol>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">\u2705 Hierarchical \u2014 shows communities at all scales\n\u274c Slow (<marimo-tex class=\"arithmatex\">||(\\mathcal{O}(E^2 V)||)</marimo-tex>) \u2014 impractical for large graphs</span></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
    },
    {
